title: Imaging Tools For The Analysis of Microvessel and Angiogenesis   Development in a Tridimensional Cell Culture System.
publication: IEEE Series International Conference on Instrument Control and Automation ( ICA )
abstract: This study presents the design and validation of imaging tools to access and analyses the development of microvessel and angiogenesis inside a tridimensional (3D) cell culture system. Angiogenesis is a key mechanism during normal development as well as in cancer cell growth. Phase contrast, fluorescence, and confocal microscopy were used to determine the cell attachment, tube-like structure formation and other cellular events inside our 3D system.
